    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="Several counties have elevated levels of poor and borderline food consumption including Juba (91 percent ), Akobo (96 percent ), Canal/Pigi (100 percent ), Nyirol (94 percent ), Pibor (97 percent ), Rumbek North (96 percent ) Bailet (94 percent ), Maban (99 percent ) and Nagero (95 percent ) where 9 in 10 households consumed very poor diets. Similarly, at least 8 in 10 households in the counties of Kajo-keji, Lainya, Terekeka, Magwi, Ayod, Awerial, Rumbek Centre, Wulu, Yirol East, Leer, Malakal, Ulang, Raja, Wau and Ibba had nutritionally inadequate diets consisting mostly of cereals with very little else during the week preceding the assessment.(December 2019)"/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 47 60 73 86 99 112 125 138 151 164 177 190 203 216 229 242 255 268 281 294 307 320 333 346 359 372 385 398 411 424 437 450 463 476 489 502 515 528 541 554 567 580 593 606 619 632 645 658 671 684 697 710 723 736 749 762 775 788 801 814 827 840 853 866 879 892 905 918 931 944 957 970 983 996 1009 1022 1035 1048 1061 1074 1087 1100 1113 1126 1139 1152 1165 1178 1191 1204 1217 1230 1243 1256 1269 1282 1295 1308 1321 1334 1347 1360 1373 1386 1399 1412 1425 1438 1451 1464 1477 1490 1503 1516 1529 1542 1555 1568 1581 1594 1607 1620 1633 1646 1659 1672 1685 1698 1711 1724 1737 1750 1763 1776 1789 1802 1815 1828 1841 1854 1867 1880 1893 1898 1903 1908 1913 1918 1923 1928 2098 2103 2046 2036 2041 1947 2072 2136 2151 2141 2146 2156 2203 1933 1940 1952 1959 1966 1973 1980 2108 2115 1987 1994 2001 2008 2015 2022 2029 2051 2058 2065 2122 2129 2077 2084 2091 2161 2168 2175 2182 2189 2196 2208 2215 2222 2229 2236 2239 2232 2243 2256"/>
